query.result:
139 You, so that you do not make yourself wonder,
140 think that there is no one on earth who governs;
141 whence so strays the human family.

142 But before January completely turns cold 143 for the hundredth [star] that is down there neglected, 144 will shine so these supreme circles,
145 that the fortune that is so awaited, 146 will turn the breasts where are the prows, 147 so that the lineage will run directly;
